Now the boss was really unhappy with the employee for procrastinating.
现在老板对员工拖延非常不满。

74
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,680
Procrastinating.
拖延。

75
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,680
Procrastinating.
拖延。

76
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,720
So the verb is to procrastinate.
所以动词是“拖延”。

77
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:15,000
And when you procrastinate you say I'll do it later I'll do it tomorrow.
当你拖延时，你会说“我晚点再做”、“我明天再做”。

78
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,680
OK so you kind of delay things or you leave it for another day.
好的，所以你有点推迟事情，或者留到另一天。

79
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,680
Yeah.
是的。

80
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,680
All right.
好的。

81
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,680
Very good.
非常好。

82
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:22,680
So to procrastinate.
所以是“拖延”。

83
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,800
A favorite verb amongst college students.
大学生最喜欢的动词。

84
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:32,040
I actually thought for a little while that procrastinate was to have babies.
我其实有一阵子以为“拖延”是生孩子。

85
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,040
Oh.
哦。

86
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,040
Oh.
哦。

87
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,040
OK.
好的。

88
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,040
It's kind of similar.
有点相似。

89
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,040
What's the word.
那个词是什么？

90
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,040
Procreate.
生育。

91
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,040
Procreate.
生育。

92
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,840
So I thought procrastinate was like having babies like why are you procrastinating.
所以我以为“拖延”就像生孩子，比如“你为什么在拖延？”

93
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,800
And I'm like I'm not.
然后我说“我没有”。

94
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,480
Well glad you got that straight.
嗯，很高兴你搞清楚了。

95
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:49,800
So yes our listeners procrastinate is not the same as procreate.
所以是的，我们的听众，“拖延”和“生育”不一样。

96
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,800
OK.
好的。

97
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,760
I learned that the hard way.
我是通过惨痛教训学到的。

98
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,760
Yes.
是的。

99
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:57,640
Well it sounds like you had a little bit of a glitch in your understanding of language
嗯，听起来你在语言理解上有点小故障，

100
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,160
and that's our next phrase.
这就是我们的下一个短语。

101
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:03,760
So in the dialogue they were talking about some glitches with the system.
所以在对话中，他们谈到了一些系统故障。

102
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:05,600
A glitch in the system.
系统故障。

103
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:06,600
OK.
好的。

104
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,600
So a glitch.
所以是“故障”。

105
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,000
Now this is common among computers right.
这在电脑中很常见，对吧？

106
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,920
A glitch is an error.
故障就是错误。

107
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,920
Right.
对。

108
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:16,200
So when you're talking about a glitch and you're talking about computers it's an error
所以当你谈论故障，并且你在谈论电脑时，它是一个错误、

109
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,280
a mistake.
一个失误。

110
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:20,760
But we also use it to talk about any unexpected problem.
但我们也用它来谈论任何意想不到的问题。

111
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:22,440
A small unexpected problem.
一个小的意想不到的问题。

112
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,440
OK.
好的。

113
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,440
So a small glitch.
所以一个小故障。

114
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,440
Yeah.
是的。

115
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:28,700
There was a glitch in our plan and we arrived 10 minutes late.
我们的计划出了个小故障，我们迟到了 10 分钟。

116
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:32,580
Or I can say this movie has a glitch in the story.
或者我可以说这部电影的故事有个故障。

117
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:35,480
So there's a small problem in the story that doesn't make sense.
所以故事里有个小问题，说不通。

118
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,480
Exactly.
没错。

119
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,480
All right.
好的。

120
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:43,320
So the boss was blaming his lateness on these small technical glitches.
所以老板把他的延误归咎于这些小技术故障。

121
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,760
But the boss didn't believe this right.
但老板不相信这个，对吧？

122
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:50,800
The boss said you're trying to rationalize the fact that you missed the deadline.
老板说你在试图合理化你错过截止日期的事实。

123
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,800
OK.
好的。

124
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,240
To rationalize.
合理化。

125
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,700
To rationalize.
合理化。

126
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:58,160
So the boss is saying that he's trying to rationalize.
所以老板说他在试图合理化。

127
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:02,080
So that means is he trying to make sense of it.
那意味着他在试图让它说得通吗？

128
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:05,680
Well this is an interesting psychological word.
嗯，这是一个有趣的心理学词汇。

129
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:10,640
Because when you rationalize something you think about it or describe it like especially
因为当你合理化某件事时，你会思考或描述它，尤其是

130
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:17,900
some bad behavior in a way that makes it seem better or proper or more sensible.
一些不好的行为，以一种让它看起来更好、更恰当或更合理的方式。

131
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:20,400
So you're trying to convince yourself.
所以你在试图说服自己。

132
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,400
Yeah.
是的。

133
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:24,440
You're telling other people but you're also telling yourself that it's better.
你在告诉别人，但也在告诉自己它更好。

134
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,440
OK.
好的。

135
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,080
Or that you're right when you're actually wrong.
或者你是对的，而实际上你是错的。

136
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,080
Yes.
是的。

137
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,080
Yeah.
是的。

138
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,080
OK.
好的。

139
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,780
So he was trying to rationalize the fact that he missed the deadline.
所以他试图合理化他错过截止日期的事实。

140
00:06:31,780 --> 00:06:36,960
So he was trying to explain to the boss and also kind of make himself believe that it
所以他试图向老板解释，同时也让自己相信

141
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:39,360
wasn't really his fault when it was.
这真的不是他的错，而实际上是他的错。

142
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:43,680
Now because this is a little bit of a difficult concept to understand I think we should hear
因为这是一个有点难理解的概念，我认为我们应该听一些

143
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,680
some examples.
例子。

144
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,460
Example one.
例子一。

145
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:53,680
You can't rationalize your son's behavior by saying he's going through a hard time.
你不能通过说他正在经历困难时期来合理化你儿子的行为。

146
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,120
Example two.
例子二。

147
00:06:56,120 --> 00:07:02,440
As much as I tried I couldn't rationalize buying such an expensive pair of shoes.
尽管我努力了，我还是无法合理化买这么贵的一双鞋。

148
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:05,140
Example three.
例子三。

149
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:06,920
You know it was the wrong thing to do.
你知道那是错事。

150
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:09,520
Stop trying to rationalize it.
别再试图合理化它了。

151
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,520
OK.
好的。

152
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:13,480
So clear as daylight now this word rationalize.
所以现在这个词“合理化”非常清楚了。

153
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,960
All right.
好的。

154
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,280
In our final word.
最后一个词。

155
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:23,080
So the boss really wasn't happy with these excuses and he said no more phony excuses.
所以老板对这些借口非常不满，他说“别再找虚假的借口了”。

156
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,080
OK.
好的。

157
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:25,080
Phony.
虚假的。

158
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,080
Phony.
虚假的。

159
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,080
P-H-O-N-Y.
P-H-O-N-Y。

160
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,080
Phony.
虚假的。

161
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:31,680
So phony is basically false or fake.
所以“虚假的”基本上就是假的或伪造的。

162
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,680
Right.
对。

163
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,680
So a phony statement.
所以一个虚假的陈述。

164
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,240
A phony watch.
一块假表。

165
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,240
OK.
好的。

166
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,240
A fake watch.
一块假表。

167
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,240
Yeah.
是的。

168
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,240
Not a Sony watch but a phony watch.
不是索尼表，而是假表。

169
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,240
A phony.
假的。

170
